22. Launching Python Programs from Outside IDLE

- Shebang line tells computer what to use to run
   * #! filepath to python
   * OS specific
   * Windows: #! python3
- run from command prompt or directly from run
   * from run closes immediately when script done
- pause.exe to wait in command line
- call @pyw instead of @py wont open a new window
- add directory to PATH, will let windows check 
    * control panel -> system -> advanced system -> environment variables
- *% forwards parameters from run/batch to python script
    * *% should be placed in the batch file
